Q.   I thought you were going to go in the lake?
NICK WATNEY:   We decided before, but I guess chickened out.

Q.   48‑degree wedge? 
NICK WATNEY:   55.

Q.   55? 
NICK WATNEY:   Yeah.

Q.   Lots of chest pumps over there?
NICK WATNEY:   I'm not sure what that was.   It was a‑‑

Q.   Spur of the moment?
NICK WATNEY:   Yeah, it was definitely not playing.   I'm sure we looked like fools, but it was fun.

Q.   How many holes‑in‑ones is this for you now? 
NICK WATNEY:   I think it's six.

Q.   You didn't jump in the lake.   He said he was going to jump in the lake, but he didn't jump in the lake. 
NICK WATNEY:   I think six, but the first one when it's actually been in a tournament.

Q.   Gets you to 4‑under, which is the lead.   Is that a good thing? 
NICK WATNEY:   Yeah, I mean, you know, curses are made to be broken.   I'm sure there will be‑‑ somebody will come and beat me anyway.

Q.   Ernie is third?
NICK WATNEY:   Yeah.   Hey, if that happens then the Red Sox won and‑‑

Q.   Does it mean anything for this week?   Does it bode well for you?
NICK WATNEY:   I hope so.   I saw him playing pretty well.   I guess my wedge game is pretty good.   I'm looking for the tournament.

Q.   What are you doing to do with the ball?
NICK WATNEY:   I'm going to save it.   Not quite sure what I'm going to do exactly, but I'll save it.

Q.   Keep the wedge too, though? 
NICK WATNEY:   Yeah, probably.

Q.   Got to keep the wedge?
NICK WATNEY:   All right.







